History of Present Illness (HPI): Patient experiences fluctuations in emotional state, feeling anxious about the future and overwhelmed by personal responsibilities, particularly concerning family dynamics and support for a spouse
Physiological Observations: Patient reports slight improvement in sleep quality and a more balanced mood, although anxiety persists during moments of uncertainty
Current Functional Status: Patient has scheduled a physical therapy appointment and expresses a desire to regain strength for hiking without pain
Therapeutic Interventions: Patient finds journaling helpful for managing emotions and is open to incorporating grounding exercises into their routine to cope with anxiety
Next Steps: Patient is encouraged to maintain communication with their spouse and to schedule regular check-ins to support each other, as well as to revisit therapy goals in future sessions
